Concepts of information, system, model, information system (IS) and information and communication technology (ICT). Purpose of IS. ICT in the society and in an organisation, ICT management, outsourcing, trends. ICT personnel, platform and services. ICT security. IS functionality, user experience etc. Analysis of problems related to ICT. ICT management and development frameworks. Organisation of request for proposals. Models for the analysis and design of organisations and IS. Analysis of IS development requirements (project). Deploying of IS.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Knowledge about management of ICT and Information Systems in organizations, frameworks for developing and managind e services.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows basic concepts and trends of ICT/IS; 2) knows how to manage and outsource ICT services; 3) should be able to estimate ICT cost structure in organisation; 4) should be able to distinguish between different areas of e-services; 5) should be able to estimate the value and need for different software in organisation.
